{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016fzxpNuWtegmLEn82hFVTK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     5→import lombok.*;\n     6→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.application.framework.EntityBase;\n     7→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.application.framework.EntityBaseObject;\n     8→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.Pet;\n     9→\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n    11→\n    12→import java.util.Date;\n    13→import java.util.Objects;\n    14→import java.util.UUID;\n    15→\n    16→/**\n    17→ * Created with IntelliJ IDEA.\n    18→ * User: tw\n    19→ * Date: 01.01.14\n    20→ * Time: 21:10\n    21→ * To change this template use File | Settings | File Templates.\n    22→ */\n    23→@Entity\n    24→@Getter\n    25→@Setter\n    26→@ToString(exclude = {\"pet\"})\n    27→@NoArgsConstructor\n    28→@AllArgsConstructor\n    29→@Table(\n    30→        name = Visit.TABLENAME,\n    31→        uniqueConstraints = {\n    32→                @UniqueConstraint(\n    33→                        name = Visit.TABLENAME + \"_unique_uuid\",\n    34→                        columnNames = {\n    35→                                Visit.COL_UUID\n    36→                        }\n    37→                ),\n    38→                @UniqueConstraint(\n    39→                        name = Visit.TABLENAME + \"_unique_names\",\n    40→                        columnNames = {\n    41→                                Visit.COL_VISIT_DATE,\n    42→                                Visit.COL_DESCRIPTION,\n    43→                                Visit.COL_PET_ID\n    44→                        }\n    45→                )\n    46→        }\n    47→)\n    48→@NamedQueries({\n    49→        @NamedQuery(\n    50→                name = \"Visit.getAll\",\n    51→                query = \"select s from Visit s order by s.date\"\n    52→        ),\n    53→        @NamedQuery(\n    54→                name = \"Visit.getVisits\",\n    55→                query = \"select v from Visit v where v.pet=:pet order by v.date\"\n    56→        )\n    57→})\n    58→public class Visit extends EntityBaseObject implements EntityBase,Comparable<Visit> {\n    59→\n    60→    public final static String TABLENAME = \"owner_pet_visit\";\n    61→    public final static String COL_ID = \"id\";\n    62→    public final static String COL_UUID = \"uuid\";\n    63→    public final static String COL_VISIT_DATE = \"visit_date\";\n    64→    public final static String COL_DESCRIPTION = \"description\";\n    65→    public final static String COL_PET_ID = \"owner_pet_id\";\n    66→    public final static String COL_SEARCHINDEX = \"searchindex\";\n    67→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2357446696894656827L;\n    68→\n    69→    @Id\n    70→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE, generator = \"owner_pet_visit_gen\")\n    71→    @SequenceGenerator(name=\"owner_pet_visit_gen\", sequenceName=\"owner_pet_visit_seq\")\n    72→    private Long id;\n    73→\n    74→    @Column(name = COL_UUID, nullable = false, unique = true, length = 36)\n    75→    private UUID uuid;\n    76→\n    77→    @Column(name = COL_SEARCHINDEX)\n    78→    private String searchindex;\n    79→\n    80→    @NotNull\n    81→    @Column(name = COL_VISIT_DATE, nullable = false)\n    82→    @Temporal(TemporalType.DATE)\n    83→    protected Date date;\n    84→\n    85→    @NotEmpty\n    86→    @Column(name = COL_DESCRIPTION, nullable = false)\n    87→    private String description;\n    88→\n    89→    @ManyToOne(\n    90→            fetch = FetchType.EAGER,\n    91→            cascade={CascadeType.REFRESH,CascadeType.DETACH, CascadeType.MERGE},\n    92→            targetEntity=Pet.class,\n    93→            optional=false\n    94→    )\n    95→    @JoinColumn(name = COL_PET_ID)\n    96→    private Pet pet;\n    97→\n    98→    @Transient\n    99→    @Override\n   100→    public String getTableName() {\n   101→        return TABLENAME;\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    @Transient\n   105→    @Override\n   106→    public String getPrimaryKey() {\n   107→        String primaryKey = description;\n   108→        return primaryKey + \" ( \" + date + \" )\";\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    @Transient\n   112→    @Override\n   113→    public String getPrimaryKeyWithId() {\n   114→        return this.getPrimaryKey() + \"(\" + this.getId() + \",\" + this.getUuid() + \")\";\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    @Transient\n   118→    @Override\n   119→    public void updateSearchindex() {\n   120→        String element1[] = this.getDate().toInstant().toString().split(\"\\\\W\");\n   121→        String element2[] = this.getDescription().split(\"\\\\W\");\n   122→        StringBuilder b = new StringBuilder();\n   123→        for(String e: element1){\n   124→            b.append(e);\n   125→            b.append(\" \");\n   126→        }\n   127→        for(String e: element2) {\n   128→            b.append(e);\n   129→            b.append(\" \");\n   130→        }\n   131→        this.setSearchindex(b.toString());\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    @Override\n   135→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   136→        if (this == o) return true;\n   137→        if (!(o instanceof Visit)) return false;\n   138→        Visit visit = (Visit) o;\n   139→        return Objects.equals(getDate(), visit.getDate()) && Objects.equals(getDescription(), visit.getDescription()) && Objects.equals(getPet(), visit.getPet());\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    @Override\n   143→    public int hashCode() {\n   144→        return Objects.hash(getDate(), getDescription());\n   145→    }\n   146→\n   147→    @Override\n   148→    public int compareTo(Visit o) {\n   149→        return this.date.compareTo(o.date);\n   150→    }\n   151→}\n   152→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Vsmpkqww9HVwJyvDR3EiuF","session_id":"8a6bcbcb-6946-47c7-9325-248dd051e737","uuid":"12722bce-80e7-4be2-acda-4b61c68953d2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Vsmpkqww9HVwJyvDR3EiuF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll compile the detailed mapping for each entity, focusing on table names, column names, join columns, and auto-mapped fields:\n\n1. Owner Entity:\n- Table Name: \"owner\"\n- Explicit Column Names (annotation name vs actual DB column):\n  - \"uuid\" -> \"uuid\"\n  - \"first_name\" -> \"first_name\"\n  - \"lastName\" -> \"last_name\" (note the camelCase converted to snake_case)\n  - \"address\" -> \"address\"\n  - \"housenumber\" -> \"housenumber\"\n  - \"address_info\" -> \"address_info\"\n  - \"city\" -> \"city\"\n  - \"zipcode\" -> \"zipcode\"\n  - \"phonenumber\" -> \"phonenumber\"\n  - \"email\" -> \"email\"\n  - \"searchindex\" -> \"searchindex\"\n- Join Columns: None\n- Auto-mapped Fields: \n  - id (will become \"id\")\n  - houseNumber (will become \"house_number\")\n\n2. Pet Entity:\n- Table Name: \"owner_pet\"\n- Explicit Column Names:\n  - \"uuid\" -> \"uuid\"\n  - \"searchindex\" -> \"searchindex\"\n  - \"birth_date\" -> \"birth_date\"\n  - \"name\" -> \"name\"\n- Join Columns:\n  - \"owner_pet_pettype_id\" (for PetType)\n  - \"owner_id\" (for Owner)\n- Auto-mapped Fields:\n  - id (will become \"id\")\n\n3. PetType Entity:\n- Table Name: \"owner_pet_pettype\"\n- Explicit Column Names:\n  - \"uuid\" -> \"uuid\"\n  - \"searchindex\" -> \"searchindex\"\n  - \"name\" -> \"name\"\n- Join Columns: None\n- Auto-mapped Fields:\n  - id (will become \"id\")\n\n4. Vet Entity:\n- Table Name: \"vet\"\n- Explicit Column Names:\n  - \"uuid\" -> \"uuid\"\n  - \"searchindex\" -> \"searchindex\"\n  - \"first_name\" -> \"first_name\"\n  - \"lastName\" -> \"last_name\"\n- Join Table/Columns:\n  - Join Table Name: \"vet_specialties\"\n  - Join Columns: \n    - \"vet_id\"\n    - \"specialty_id\"\n- Auto-mapped Fields:\n  - id (will become \"id\")\n\n5. Specialty Entity:\n- Table Name: \"specialty\"\n- Explicit Column Names:\n  - \"uuid\" -> \"uuid\"\n  - \"searchindex\" -> \"searchindex\"\n  - \"name\" -> \"name\"\n- Join Columns: None\n- Auto-mapped Fields:\n  - id (will become \"id\")\n\n6. Visit Entity:\n- Table Name: \"owner_pet_visit\"\n- Explicit Column Names:\n  - \"uuid\" -> \"uuid\"\n  - \"searchindex\" -> \"searchindex\"\n  - \"visit_date\" -> \"visit_date\"\n  - \"description\" -> \"description\"\n- Join Columns:\n  - \"owner_pet_id\" (for Pet)\n- Auto-mapped Fields:\n  - id (will become \"id\")\n\nKey Observations:\n1. The SpringPhysicalNamingStrategy converts camelCase to snake_case, even for explicitly named columns.\n2. Some tables use composite names like \"owner_pet_visit\" to represent relationships.\n3. Most entities follow a consistent pattern of having uuid, searchindex, and id columns.\n4. Each entity has unique constraints on specific combinations of columns.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of these column mappings?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a6bcbcb-6946-47c7-9325-248dd051e737","uuid":"02ad7485-afa3-4a3e-9b94-dcace2116606"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_013R13aF3J5HZsKBSqsPPRjq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the issue. The key problem is that Spring Boot's `SpringPhysicalNamingStrategy` converts:\n- `lastName` (annotation) → `last_name` (actual DB column)\n\nBut the data.sql uses `lastname` as the column name. The simplest approach is to set the Hibernate physical naming strategy to use column names exactly as specified in `@Column(name=...)` annotations. Let me update `application.properties` and also fix the data.sql column names.\n\nActually, the cleanest fix is to set `spring.jpa.hibernate.naming.physical-strategy=org.hibernate.boot.model.naming.PhysicalNamingStrategyStandardImpl` which uses column names exactly as provided. This way `@Column(name=\"lastName\")` becomes column `lastName` in DB (which PostgreSQL lowercases to `lastname`), matching the data.sql."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1791,"cache_read_input_tokens":64290,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1791,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":462},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a6bcbcb-6946-47c7-9325-248dd051e737","uuid":"b76620c0-6f33-4dc3-9c4d-b3aaad5ae2d9"}
