{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014k7UwKVFovfALnABWkTZUD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks are complete. Here's a summary of the migration:\n\n## Migration Complete: Jakarta EE 10 -> Spring Boot 3.2.5\n\n**All 18 smoke tests passed (18/18).**\n\n### Key changes:\n- **pom.xml**: Replaced ~5000-line Jakarta EE POM with Spring Boot 3.2.5 parent POM, changed packaging from WAR to JAR, Java 11 -> 17\n- **Data Access**: DAO pattern (12 files) replaced with 6 Spring Data JPA Repository interfaces\n- **Services**: EJB `@Stateless` beans replaced with Spring `@Service` + `@Transactional`\n- **REST API**: JAX-RS endpoints rewritten as Spring `@RestController` classes\n- **Web UI**: JSF/PrimeFaces XHTML views replaced with 12 Thymeleaf templates + 5 Spring MVC controllers\n- **DTOs**: JSON-B/JAXB annotations replaced with Jackson (`@JsonProperty`, `@JsonFormat`)\n- **Configuration**: Liberty `server.xml` replaced with `application.properties`\n- **Dockerfile**: Updated from `mvn clean liberty:run` to building a Spring Boot JAR and running with `java -jar`\n\n### Error encountered and resolved:\n- Column name mismatch due to Spring Boot's default naming strategy converting `lastName` to `last_name`. Fixed by configuring `PhysicalNamingStrategyStandardImpl` to preserve explicit `@Column` names."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":424,"cache_read_input_tokens":89729,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":424,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":353},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8a6bcbcb-6946-47c7-9325-248dd051e737","uuid":"70c1aa6d-909e-4827-8f11-a12d5dc386fd"}
